sentences: Jim Stewart (born July 29, 1930) is an American record executive and record producer who co-founded Stax Records, one of the leading recording companies during soul and R&B music's heydays in the 1960s and 1970s.
Raised on a farm in Middleton, Tennessee, Stewart moved to Memphis in 1948 after graduating from high school.
After serving for two years, Stewart returned to his job as a bank clerk in Memphis in 1953.
In 1957, Stewart launched his own record label, then called Satellite Records, which issued country music and rockabilly records.
In 1959, the label moved into the former Capitol Theatre in Memphis.
After selling millions of records during its history, Stax went bankrupt in 1976.
When he was inducted into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame in 2002, he sent his granddaughter Jennifer to the induction ceremony to accept the award on his behalf.
